XLIV THE INTERIM OF AUGSBURG

When Luther died, 18 Feb. 1546, the last obstacle to war was removed. The Emperor, allying himself, 19 June, with Maurice, Duke of Saxony, and, 26 June, with the Pope, outlawed, 20 July, the Elector and the Landgrave3 and Maurice, cousin of the one and son-in-law of the other, seized his opportunity to rise, by the imperial favour, on the ruin of both.
